y 2020, the Shadow Cabinet of the SNP in Westminster was as follows.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.uk/mps-lords-and-offices/government-and-opposition1/scottish-national-party/|title=Scottish National Party Spokespersons|website=UK Parliament|language=English|access-date=2019-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524075054/https://www.parliament.uk/mps-lords-and-offices/government-and-opposition1/scottish-national-party/|archive-date=24 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"  style=\"font-size:97%\"\n|-\n! Portfolio  !! Shadow Secretary/Minister\n|-\n|'''Westminster Leader'''\n| [[Ian Blackford|Ian Blackford MP]] <br><small>([[Ross, Skye and Lochaber (UK Parliament constituency)|Ross, Skye and Lochaber]])</small>\n|-\n|'''Westminster Depute Leader'''\n| [[Kirsty Blackman|Kirsty Blackman MP]]<br><small>([[Aberdeen North (UK Parliament constituency)|Aberdeen North]])</small>\n|-\n| Shadow Chancellor\n| [[Alison Thewliss|Alison Thewliss MP]] <br><small>([[Glasgow Central (UK Parliament constituency)|Glasgow Central]])</small>\n|-\n| Shadow Foreign Secretary\n|[[Alyn Smith|Alyn Smith MP]] <br><small>([[Stirling (UK Parliament constituency)|Stirling]])</small>\n|-\n| Shadow Secretary of State for Health and Social Care <br> Shadow Secretary of State for Exiting the EU\n|[[Philippa Whitford|Dr Philippa Whitford MP]] <br><small>([[Central Ayrshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Central Ayrshire]])</small>\n|-\n| Shadow Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport\n|[[John Nicolson|John Nicolson MP]] <br><small>([[Ochil and South Perthshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Ochil and South Perthshire]])</small>\n|-\n| Shadow Secretary of State for Scotland\n| [[Mhairi Black|Mhairi Black MP]] <br><small>([[Paisley and Renfrewshire South (UK Parliament constituency)|Paisley and Renfrewshire South]])</small>\n|-\n| Shadow Secretary of State for Northern Ireland and Wales\n|[[Kirsten Oswald|Kirsten Oswald MP]] <br><small>([[East Re