ational Party/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 12\n|{{steady}} '''1st'''\n|{{steady}} 3rd\n|{{no2|Opposition}}\n|}\n\n===Local Councils===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year<ref name=\"The Scottish National Party\"/>\n ! Share of votes !! Seats won !! Notes\n|-\n| [[1995 Scottish local elections|1995]]||26.1%||{{Composition bar|181|1222|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||\n|-\n| [[1999 Scottish local elections|1999]]||28.9%||{{Composition bar|201|1222|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||\n|-\n| [[2003 Scottish local elections|2003]]||24.1%||{{Composition bar|171|1222|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||\n|-\n| [[2007 Scottish local elections|2007]]||29.7% (first preference)||{{Composition bar|363|1222|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||Largest party in [[local government in Scotland|local government]] (first Scottish local elections to be held under the [[single transferable vote]]).\n|-\n| [[2012 Scottish local elections|2012]]||32.3% (first preference)||{{Composition bar|425|1223|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||Largest party in local government; received largest number of first preference votes.\n|-\n| [[2017 Scottish local elections|2017]]||32.3% (first preference)||{{Composition bar|431|1227|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||Largest party in local government; received largest number of first preference votes.\nBest ever SNP local election result.\n|}\n\n===European Parliament===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year<ref name=\"The Scottish National Party\"/>\n ! Share of votes !! Seats won !! Notes\n|-\n| [[1979 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1979]]|| 19.4% ||{{Composition bar|1|8|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||\n|-\n| [[1984 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1984]]|| {{decrease}} 17.8% ||{{Composition b